Tantech Holdings Ltd Key Developments

Tantech Holdings Ltd Obtains Official Approval for Two Updated EV Models
Jul 25 17
Tantech Holdings Ltd. announced that the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China (MIIT) has included two of its updated electric vehicle models in the 'Announcement of Road Motor Vehicle Manufacturing Enterprises and Products'. The two vehicles are produced by the company's subsidiary Suzhou E Motors Buses Co. Ltd. So far, together with previous approvals from the MIIT, the Company has recognized approvals in a total of 11 electric vehicles models. The new updated electric bus ZQK6810EV6, one of the two latest models approved by the MIIT, has much higher quality energy intensity and durability compared to previous model ZQK6810EV. It is driven by an updated lithium iron phosphate battery. With a range of more than 300 km (186 miles), the 8.1-meter-long bus can travel as fast as 120 km/h (75mph) and carry as many as 34 passengers. The bus is particularly suited for use as shuttle buses at tourist attractions and airports, or as commuter buses for local communities. ZQK6810EV8, the other model approved by the MIIT, is a newly designed urban electric bus for city transportation. The bus, 8.1-meters long and powered by electric motors, is equipped with brand new chassis and suspension system. It has a greater carrying capacity and less weight. It travels as fast as 100 km/h (62 mph) with a range of 300 km range on a single charge. The bus carries as many as 46 passengers. It will be a preferred choice for preferred public transportation in major cities and towns. The bus has been put into the trial phase in a few Northern China cities by local bus companies.


Tantech Seeks Acquisitions
Jul 17 17
Tantech Holdings Ltd (NasdaqCM:TANH) plans to continue expanding and diversifying their products by developing and acquiring more eco-friendly assets in the future.


Tantech Holdings Ltd Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year of 2017
May 1 17
Tantech Holdings Ltd. reported consolidated earnings results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported revenues of $47,665,674 compared to $58,829,900 a year ago. Income from operations was of $6,295,491 compared to $10,214,442 a year ago. Income before income taxes was of $5,974,963 compared to $11,304,468 a year ago. Net income attributable to common stockholders were of $4,299,251 or $0.19 per basic and diluted share compared to $8,438,825 or $0.40 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities were of $7,033,052 compared to net cash provided by operating activities of $4,450,532 a year ago. Additions to property, plant and equipment were of $10,819 compared to $242,552 a year ago. 

The company expects increased revenue and earnings growth in 2017 and beyond driven by innovation, new business development initiatives and more streamlined operations.


